messages.message:
Hey team, when running `make test COVERAGE=True OPEN_REPORT=True`, I've been getting the following mypy errors
```TYPECHECKING FAILURE: mypy exited with code 1

instabase/solution_utils/marketplace.py:15: error: Library stubs not installed for "requests" (or incompatible with Python 3.7)
instabase/solution_utils/marketplace.py:15: note: Hint: "python3 -m pip install types-requests"```
using `pyenv global 3.9.15` doesnt seem to change the output, nor does using the hinted command. Does anyone know how to fix this?
what folder are you running tests from?
what does `mypy --version` get you? also do you get the same error with just `make test` (no coverage/open_report)?
`mypy 0.981 (compiled: no)` and yep yep the error is the same
ah, that's too new â€” try `pip install mypy==0.701` (and make sure you are back on python 3.7)
